results.name: Number of binary words of length n with exactly k (possibly overlapping) occurrences of the subword given by the binary expansion of n for maximal k with at least one word.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
example: a(4) = 4 because there are 4 binary words of length 4 with one occurrence of 100, namely 0100, 1000, 1001, 1100, and no words with more than one occurrence of 100.
xref: Last (positive) terms of rows of A233940.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Dec 18 2013
